## Unique Knowledge

### 1. Stale Closure Prevention Pattern
The project explicitly avoids React hooks for animation state because of stale closures:

```typescript
// WRONG - causes stale closures
const [zoom, setZoom] = useState(1);
const animateRef = useRef({ animate: () => { /* stale zoom */ } });

// CORRECT - uses external store
const animate = () => {
  const state = canvasStore.getState(); // Always current
  const zoom = state.viewport.camera.zoom;
  // Use fresh zoom value
};
```

### 2. Dynamic Min Zoom Calculation
Min zoom is calculated dynamically to prevent white space:

```typescript
const effectiveMinZoom = useMemo(() => {
  const worldWidth = worldBounds.maxX - worldBounds.minX;
  const worldHeight = Math.abs(worldBounds.maxY - worldBounds.minY);
  const minZoomX = canvasSize.width / worldWidth;
  const minZoomY = canvasSize.height / worldHeight;
  return Math.max(ABSOLUTE_MIN_ZOOM, Math.max(minZoomX, minZoomY));
}, [canvasSize, worldBounds]);
```

### 3. Trackpad vs Mouse Detection
Detects input device by event frequency:

```typescript
const TRACKPAD_DETECTION_THRESHOLD = 20; // ms
const TRACKPAD_EVENT_COUNT_THRESHOLD = 3;

// Events faster than 20ms apart = trackpad
// Mouse events are typically spaced further apart
```

### 4. World-to-Screen Coordinate Conversion
```typescript
// Screen to world
const worldX = cameraX - halfViewX + (canvasX / zoom);
const worldY = cameraY + halfViewY - (canvasY / zoom);

// World to screen
const screenX = (worldX - cameraX + halfViewX) * zoom;
const screenY = (cameraY + halfViewY - worldY) * zoom;
```

### 5. Easing Functions for Animation
```typescript
const Easing = {
  quadOut: (t: number) => t * (2 - t),      // Google Maps style
  cubicOut: (t: number) => 1 - Math.pow(1 - t, 3),
};
```

### 6. Viewport Bounds for Culling
```typescript
const viewportBounds: ViewportBounds = {
  minX: cameraPos.x - (canvasSize.width / 2 / zoom),
  maxX: cameraPos.x + (canvasSize.width / 2 / zoom),
  minY: cameraPos.y - (canvasSize.height / 2 / zoom),
  maxY: cameraPos.y + (canvasSize.height / 2 / zoom),
};
```

### 7. Task Hit Testing
```typescript
function findTaskAtPosition(screenX, screenY, containerRect, camera, zoom, tasks) {
  const canvasX = screenX - containerRect.left;
  const canvasY = screenY - containerRect.top;
  const halfViewX = canvasSize.width / 2 / zoom;
  const halfViewY = canvasSize.height / 2 / zoom;
  const worldX = camera.x - halfViewX + (canvasX / zoom);
  const worldY = camera.y + halfViewY - (canvasY / zoom);

  for (const task of tasks) {
    const taskStartX = task.startDay * pxPerDay;
    const taskEndX = taskStartX + task.duration * pxPerDay;
    const taskCenterY = -task.trainIndex * pxPerTrain - pxPerTrain / 2;
    const taskTopY = taskCenterY + TASK_HEIGHT / 2;
    const taskBottomY = taskCenterY - TASK_HEIGHT / 2;

    if (worldX >= taskStartX && worldX <= taskEndX &&
        worldY <= taskTopY && worldY >= taskBottomY) {
      return task.id;
    }
  }
  return null;
}
```

