## React Integration: useSyncExternalStore

The library uses React 18's `useSyncExternalStore` for tear-free reads:

```typescript
// From hooks.ts
function useSelector<T>(selector: (state: any) => T): T {
  return React.useSyncExternalStore(store.subscribe, () => {
    const fullState = store.getState();
    return selector(fullState);
  });
}
```

### Benefits Over useState

| Problem | useState | @zazcart/tools |
|---------|----------|----------------|
| Stale closures | Common in animation loops | Solved via getState() |
| Batched updates | Async (unreliable timing) | Synchronous |
| Re-render granularity | Coarse | Fine (selectors) |

